<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56d8492e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s3746"><num value="3746">§ 3746.</num><heading> Promotion; acceptance; oath of office</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id56d8492f-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s3746/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A Reserve officer who has been appointed under this subchapter is considered to have accepted the appointment unless delivery thereof cannot be effected.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id56d84930-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s3746/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> A Reserve officer who has served continuously since taking the oath of office prescribed in <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s3331">section 3331 of title 5</ref>, is not required to take a new oath of office upon appointment in a higher grade.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id56d84931-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/96/322/s1">Pub. L. 96–322, § 1</ref>, <date date="1980-08-04">Aug. 4, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/1012">94 Stat. 1012</ref>, § 735; renumbered § 3746, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s118/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 118(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4233">132 Stat. 4233</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56d84932-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id56d84933-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id56d84934-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s797">section 797 of this title</ref> prior to the complete revision of former chapter 21 of this title by <ref href="/us/pl/96/322">Pub. L. 96–322</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id56d84935-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—<ref href="/us/pl/115/282">Pub. L. 115–282</ref> renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s735">section 735 of this title</ref> as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
